=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains the details about a blue/green deployment.

For more information, see Using Amazon RDS Blue/Green Deployments for
database updates
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/UserGuide/blue-green-deployments.html)
in the I<Amazon RDS User Guide> and Using Amazon RDS Blue/Green
Deployments for database updates
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/AuroraUserGuide/blue-green-deployments.html)
in the I<Amazon Aurora User Guide>.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 SourceMember => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a resource in the blue environment.


=head2 Status => Str

The switchover status of a resource in a blue/green deployment.

Values:

=over

=item *

C<PROVISIONING> - The resource is being prepared to switch over.

=item *

C<AVAILABLE> - The resource is ready to switch over.

=item *

C<SWITCHOVER_IN_PROGRESS> - The resource is being switched over.

=item *

C<SWITCHOVER_COMPLETED> - The resource has been switched over.

=item *

C<SWITCHOVER_FAILED> - The resource attempted to switch over but
failed.

=item *

C<MISSING_SOURCE> - The source resource has been deleted.

=item *

C<MISSING_TARGET> - The target resource has been deleted.

=back



=head2 TargetMember => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a resource in the green environment.



